metadata.name: Strawberry Fields #1
metadata.description:
Inspired by "Strawberry Fields Forever", the highly influential song on the emerging psychedelic genre.

John Lennon viewed "Strawberry Fields Forever" as his finest work with the Beatles. The song established "the standard and style for the entire psychedelic pop movement that would follow"

"Let me take you down
'Cause I'm going to strawberry fields
Nothing is real
And nothing to get hung about
Strawberry fields forever

Living is easy with eyes closed
Misunderstanding all you see
It's getting hard to be someone but it all works out
It doesn't matter much to me"

This artwork is a tribute to the Beatles and psychedelia in general and has been crafted entirely with code in p5js (javascript) and uses Cellular Automata as a base structure.

INTERACT WITH YOUR TOKEN:

- Press ‘m’ once to render a monochromatic version of the artwork.

OR: 
   - Press ‘r’ to increase +1 the number of runs, for a more psychedelic (colorful) version of the artwork. Pressing multiple times will increase this parameter.
   - Press ‘g’ to increase +1 the glitchiness. Pressing multiple times will increase this parameter.

////// you can combine ‘r’ and ‘g’ for a composite effect /////

If:
   - you’re happy with the result, clap your hands and: 
   - Press ’s’ to save a large PNG file of your artwork, ready for print (5x current viewport size).

Else: 
   - refresh the page and start over until your achieve YOUR desired creation
   - Press ’s’ to save a large PNG file of your artwork, ready for print (5x current viewport size).

metadata.name: Composition study : Grid #157
metadata.description: This project explores the use of geometric shapes, specifically grids, cubes, and patterns, in composition. The focus will be on using these shapes and patterns to create dynamic and visually interesting compositions, both in 2D and 3D forms. The project begins by studying the use of grids and how they can be used to create structure and balance in a composition. Next, the use of cubes will be examined, and how they can be used to add depth and dimension to a composition. Finally, the project will delve into the use of patterns and how they can be used to create movement and interest within a composition.

metadata.name: Insula #1
metadata.description:
An audiovisual collection.
.
Click to start the sound.
..
Insula is an endless generative music player.
...
There are 6 different grid size; 4 squares and 20 squares are the rare ones.

2 different background texture; Lines, Grain.

2 different color placement; Circular, Linear.

7 different noise types.

8 different scales with fixed root notes; C Maj., C Lydian, D Dorian, D Min. Penta., G Maj., G Maj. Penta., F Mixolydian, F Min.

2 different rhythmical structures; 2:3, 4:5.

2 different note indicator style; Circle and Square. Square is rare and behaves differently.

5 different note indicator line divisions.
....
Harmonization process based on Avro Part's 'Tintinnabuli' style.

Grid design inspired from Novation's Launchpad.


Made with p5.js and Web Audio.

Ilgın İçözü, December 2021
@distcollective

metadata.name: de|growth:generations #28
metadata.description:
Materials tend to take particular forms due to their physical properties, technological necessities or natural limitations. However, what rules should a simulated environment follow when no physical constraints are inherent to the digital environment?

This project continues the exploration of shaping digital matter that I began on hicetnunc in 2021. Each token creates an image of a unique sculpture generated with a custom growth/degrowth algorithm. The image is rendered with a tailored raytracing script.

---
Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones for the 800x800px image.

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the resolution from preview quality to a print of approx. 30x30cm. There may be minor differences in tone or contrast for different resolutions.

In live mode:
Click PNG to save the rendered image.
Click STL to download the digital model to view on your computer or 3d print at home [experimental]

metadata.name: Specter of Fears #97
metadata.description:
In the dreamlike landscape of our minds, the specter of fears is like a wraith, ever-present and ethereal. It whispers in our ear, reminding us of all the things we dare not face. It is a shadow that falls across our hearts, casting a pall of doubt and uncertainty. But even as it haunts us, we must remember that it is a part of us. We must learn to accept its presence, and to use it to our advantage. For fear is not always a curse, it is a guide that shows us where we must grow stronger. It is a companion that walks with us through the dark night, illuminating the path ahead. By embracing our fears, we find the courage to face them, and to overcome them. We find the strength to live fully, to love fiercely, and to pursue our dreams with abandon.

Controls :

• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

———————

metadata.name: Glossolalia #158
metadata.description:
This series is ultimately about catharsis. The compositions can be chaotic and maybe even a little messy, but they also can be vibrant and diverse… which is really what this is trying to celebrate: diversity and expression.

Simply, it’s about the emotions associated with whatever frees you.

Please see the linked fxtext article (on the main project page) for a more in-depth dissection of the concept. It’s less of a technical discussion, and more about the experience of the artist, and how it became linked with the feelings they associate with the art.

In live mode:

For higher resolutions, you can append “&density=2” to the url to double the size, “&density=3” to triple, and so on.
(This is highly recommended.)

To adjust grain, you can append “&grain=##” to the url. 40 is the default, and 0 will remove it completely.
